---
description: Anything related to Dimensions, converting AppConfig Values into 3js Units. 
alwaysApply: false
---
**Units | App Config & Three.js Conversion**
- All distance and position values in `src__AppConfig/Na__AppConfig__Main.json` are integer millimeters.
  - This is to ensure that the values are consistent vs the 3D Modeling Software (e.g. SketchUp which will be used to create the models)

**Conversions Are Required When Using App Config Values For Specifically Three.js Functions**
- Convert mm data values from App config to Three.js units using math helpers in `src__MathUtils/Na__Math__Units.js`.
- Three.js scene units are meters.
  - So 1000 mm within the App Config = 1 Unit in the Three.js scene

**Models Loaded From Glb Files Are Already Properly Scaled**
- SketchUp Glb Exporter exports units as millimeters.
  - So assume Glb models are in millimeters so already properly scaled.
